160→/// Generate a random array with bounded length, biased toward small sizes.
161→///
162→/// Most real bugs appear at boundary lengths (0, 1, 2, 3), so we heavily
163→/// favor those over larger sizes. The distribution:
164→/// - 25% chance of length 0 (empty array)
165→/// - 25% chance of length 1 (single element)
166→/// - 20% chance of length 2
